0076346e-506f-4cd7-81c2-b3154d2d9a89.7dd4e9ac-ffa5-4b0a-8e24-8ce00009908f.description=This will sort a table based upon one column in the table. If all of the entries in that column are numeric the sort will be numeric, otherwise it will be alphabetic. 
Inputs\:
Table\: the table to sort
columnDelimiter - the character used to delimit columns
rowDelimiter - the character used to delimit rows
column - the number of the column to sort on(starting at 1).
reverse - set to "true" to make the sort a reverse sort

Results\:
The sorted table output with the same row and column delimiters

Responses\:
success - if the sort completed
failure - if there was an error, for example the specified column was missing in one or more entries

0076346e-506f-4cd7-81c2-b3154d2d9a89.b0e42b20-08a0-4bab-9913-2d947400b5f2.description=
Compares two strings, returning a true response if and only if they contain the same sequence of characters. A null string is considered to be equal to an empty string.

Inputs\:
string1 - The first string.
string2 - The second string.
ignoreCase - If set to 'true', then the comparison ignores case considerations. The two strings are considered equal ignoring case if they are of the same length and corresponding characters in the two strings are equal ignoring case. If set to any value other than 'true', then the strings must match exactly to be considered equal.

responses\:
true - If the two strings are equal
false - If the two strings are not equal

0076346e-506f-4cd7-81c2-b3154d2d9a89.description=
Synopsis

    This flow retrieves the number of LIFs on a physical port.
    getNumNetLifsPerPhysPortList performs the following steps\:
      1. Retrieve the port information based on the inputs.
      2. Make an xslt list of the ports.
      3. Retrieve the LIFs for each port.
      4. Make an xslt list of the LIFs.
      5. Retrieve a list of ports based on the failover group.
      6. Retrieve a list of LIFs based on the physical port list.
      7. Sort the list of LIFs.
      8. Pass the information to the requesting entity.

Inputs

    clusterName - The IP or host name of the NetApp cluster (required).
      Valid values\: Dot-decimal notation IPv4 address or RFC 1123 compliant host name.
      Default value\: None.

    node - The contoller node for the clusterName (required).
      Valid values\: Implementation-specfic.
      Default value\: None.

    excludeFgPortRegexList - 
      Valid values\: 
      Default value\: 

    sortOrder - (required).
      Valid values\: 
      Default value\: 

    includeOnlyLinkStatusUp - (required).
      Valid values\: 
      Default value\: 

    elementDelimiter - (required).
      Valid values\: 
      Default value\: 

    tokenDelimiter - (required).
      Valid values\: 
      Default value\: 

    overrideJRAS - Value to override the system defined Java RAS server.
      Valid values\: Implementation specific.
      Default value\: Hosting Eng RAS.


Results

    hpooFlowResult - The XML response specific to the functionality of the flow; in this case a list of LIFs attached to a port.  See Notes section for more details.
    flowStatus - Overall status of the flow, value is one of the string literals "success" or "failed".

Responses

    Success - All operations and subflows completed successfully.
    Failure - Some operations and/or subflows failed.

Notes

    1. Anything else the caller or support person may need to know about the flow. Relationships that aren't easily inferred, abmnormal flow behaviors, hard-codings, etc.
